<TITLE> Banglalink to get latest Ericsson technology </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 18 (bdnews24.com) -- Orascom Telecom Holdings has selected Ericsson to provide its subsidiary Banglalink with the latest mobile technology. Ericsson will supply a network technology package that would include radio base-stations and base-station controllers to develop a network in Dhaka and its surroundings, Ericsson's Dhaka office said in a statement Monday. Ericsson said the installation of equipment would allow Banglalink to offer advanced services, such as GPRS and greater network coverage during peak hours. "By using Ericsson equipment, Banglalink will be able to offer superior network quality and enhanced communications to its end users in Bangladesh," said Tamer El Mahdy, Orascom's chief technology officer. Banglalink's chief executive officer Rashid Khan said partnership with Ericsson would ensure the network the right technological building blocks as it moved into future. Mohamed Ghidan, chief technology officer of Banglalink, said: "I am very optimistic about having Ericsson in our network due to their abilities and commitment to coverage and quality." bd
